## Color Theory & Psychological Design

Color is the most powerful tool in a designer's arsenal. Understanding color theory and psychology allows you to create designs that not only look beautiful but also evoke specific emotions and drive user behavior.

### Color Theory Fundamentals

#### The Color Wheel & Color Relationships
```css
/* Primary Colors - Cannot be created by mixing other colors */
.primary-red { color: #FF0000; }      /* Red */
.primary-blue { color: #0000FF; }    /* Blue */
.primary-yellow { color: #FFFF00; }  /* Yellow */

/* Secondary Colors - Created by mixing primary colors */
.secondary-green { color: #00FF00; } /* Blue + Yellow */
.secondary-orange { color: #FFA500; } /* Red + Yellow */
.secondary-purple { color: #800080; } /* Red + Blue */
```

#### Color Harmony Systems

**1. Complementary Colors**
```css
/* Colors opposite each other on the color wheel */
.complementary {
  background: linear-gradient(45deg, #FF6B6B, #4ECDC4);
  /* Red and Teal - High contrast, energetic */
}

/* Usage: Call-to-action buttons, alerts, important notifications */
.cta-button {
  background: #FF6B6B;
  color: #4ECDC4;
  border: 2px solid #4ECDC4;
}
```

**2. Analogous Colors**
```css
/* Colors adjacent on the color wheel */
.analogous {
  background: linear-gradient(to right,
    #FF6B6B, /* Red */
    #FFA500, /* Orange */
    #FFFF00  /* Yellow */
  );
}

/* Usage: Natural, harmonious designs, food industry */
```

**3. Triadic Colors**
```css
/* Three colors equally spaced on the color wheel */
.triadic {
  background: linear-gradient(120deg,
    #FF6B6B, /* Red */
    #4ECDC4, /* Teal */
    #45B7D1  /* Blue */
  );
}

/* Usage: Vibrant, playful designs, creative industries */
```

### Color Psychology & User Experience

#### Emotional Color Associations
```javascript
// Color Psychology Mapping
const colorPsychology = {
  red: {
    emotions: ['passion', 'energy', 'urgency'],
    associations: ['love', 'danger', 'power'],
    usage: ['call-to-action', 'warnings', 'food'],
    hex: '#FF6B6B'
  },

  blue: {
    emotions: ['trust', 'calm', 'reliability'],
    associations: ['security', 'peace', 'professionalism'],
    usage: ['corporate', 'healthcare', 'finance'],
    hex: '#4ECDC4'
  },

  green: {
    emotions: ['growth', 'harmony', 'freshness'],
    associations: ['nature', 'money', 'health'],
    usage: ['environment', 'finance', 'wellness'],
    hex: '#45B7D1'
  },

  yellow: {
    emotions: ['optimism', 'creativity', 'attention'],
    associations: ['sunshine', 'caution', 'happiness'],
    usage: ['children', 'warnings', 'energy'],
    hex: '#FFA500'
  }
};
```

#### Cultural Color Considerations
```javascript
// Cultural Color Interpretations
const culturalColors = {
  white: {
    western: 'purity, cleanliness',
    eastern: 'death, mourning',
    middleEast: 'purity, peace'
  },

  red: {
    china: 'good fortune, joy',
    western: 'danger, passion',
    india: 'purity, marriage',
    japan: 'anger, danger'
  },

  green: {
    islam: 'paradise, peace',
    western: 'nature, growth',
    ireland: 'national identity'
  }
};
```

### Practical Color Application

#### Color Contrast & Accessibility
```css
/* WCAG AA Compliant Color Combinations */
.accessible-text {
  /* Normal text: 4.5:1 contrast ratio */
  color: #333333; /* Dark gray on white */
  background: #FFFFFF;
}

.accessible-button {
  /* Large text: 3:1 contrast ratio */
  background: #0066CC; /* Blue */
  color: #FFFFFF; /* White text */
  border: 2px solid #004499;
}

/* Color Blind Friendly Palettes */
.colorblind-safe {
  background: #FFFFFF;
  color: #000000;
}

.colorblind-safe-accent {
  background: #0072B2; /* Blue */
  color: #FFFFFF;
}
```

#### Color in UI Components
```css
/* Button Variants with Semantic Colors */
.btn-primary {
  background: #007BFF;
  color: white;
  border: 1px solid #007BFF;
}

.btn-secondary {
  background: #6C757D;
  color: white;
  border: 1px solid #6C757D;
}

.btn-success {
  background: #28A745;
  color: white;
  border: 1px solid #28A745;
}

.btn-danger {
  background: #DC3545;
  color: white;
  border: 1px solid #DC3545;
}

.btn-warning {
  background: #FFC107;
  color: #212529;
  border: 1px solid #FFC107;
}
```

### Advanced Color Techniques

#### Color Temperature & Mood
```css
/* Warm vs Cool Color Schemes */
.warm-scheme {
  /* Warm colors: Reds, oranges, yellows */
  background: linear-gradient(135deg, #FF6B6B, #FFA500, #FFFF00);
}

.cool-scheme {
  /* Cool colors: Blues, greens, purples */
  background: linear-gradient(135deg, #4ECDC4, #45B7D1, #9B59B6);
}

.neutral-scheme {
  /* Neutral grays and beiges */
  background: linear-gradient(135deg, #F8F9FA, #E9ECEF, #DEE2E6);
}
```

#### Dynamic Color Systems
```javascript
// Dynamic color generation based on user preferences
const dynamicColors = {
  generatePalette: (baseColor, mood) => {
    const palettes = {
      energetic: [baseColor, lighten(baseColor, 20), darken(baseColor, 20)],
      calm: [baseColor, desaturate(baseColor, 30), lighten(baseColor, 40)],
      professional: [baseColor, '#FFFFFF', '#F8F9FA']
    };
    return palettes[mood] || [baseColor];
  },

  applyTheme: (theme) => {
    document.documentElement.style.setProperty('--primary-color', theme.primary);
    document.documentElement.style.setProperty('--secondary-color', theme.secondary);
    document.documentElement.style.setProperty('--accent-color', theme.accent);
  }
};
```

### Color Management Tools & Systems

#### Design Tokens
```javascript
// Design Token System
const designTokens = {
  colors: {
    primary: {
      50: '#EFF6FF',
      100: '#DBEAFE',
      500: '#3B82F6',
      600: '#2563EB',
      900: '#1E3A8A'
    },

    semantic: {
      success: '#10B981',
      warning: '#F59E0B',
      error: '#EF4444',
      info: '#3B82F6'
    }
  },

  spacing: {
    1: '0.25rem',
    2: '0.5rem',
    4: '1rem',
    8: '2rem'
  }
};
```

#### Color Accessibility Tools
```javascript
// Color Contrast Checker
const contrastChecker = {
  calculateRatio: (color1, color2) => {
    const l1 = getLuminance(color1);
    const l2 = getLuminance(color2);
    const ratio = (Math.max(l1, l2) + 0.05) / (Math.min(l1, l2) + 0.05);
    return Math.round(ratio * 100) / 100;
  },

  isAccessible: (ratio, size) => {
    const thresholds = {
      normal: 4.5,
      large: 3.0
    };
    return ratio >= thresholds[size];
  }
};
```

